Number 4:

86
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:55,440
Border Buddies

87
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:57,440
Aside from China and Pakistan,

88
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:58,440
India shares a land border

89
00:02:58,440 --> 00:02:59,849
with four other countries:

90
00:02:59,849 --> 00:03:02,959
Myanmar, Nepal, Bangladesh, and Bhutan.

91
00:03:02,959 --> 00:03:05,290
And the Chinese regime is spending

92
00:03:05,290 --> 00:03:07,090
billions of dollars to become friends

93
00:03:07,090 --> 00:03:08,230
with those neighbors,

94
00:03:08,230 --> 00:03:09,230
you know,

95
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:10,959
making them indebted to China,

96
00:03:10,959 --> 00:03:12,070
often literally.

97
00:03:12,070 --> 00:03:13,990
It’s part of China’s One Belt,

98
00:03:13,990 --> 00:03:15,090
One Road Initiative.

99
00:03:15,090 --> 00:03:17,080
That’s where the Chinese regime

100
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:19,260
drains developing nations of their resources

101
00:03:19,260 --> 00:03:21,300
through large-scale infrastructure projects

102
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:22,860
and massive loans,

103
00:03:22,860 --> 00:03:24,120
in exchange for making China

104
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:26,040
the economic center of the world.

105
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,300
It’s win-win.

106
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:28,300
The Chinese regime

107
00:03:28,300 --> 00:03:29,480
gets money and power,

108
00:03:29,480 --> 00:03:30,830
and the other countries get to become

109
00:03:30,830 --> 00:03:31,870
tribute states.

110
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:34,770
At least they get high-speed trains.

111
